    en: "New York Public Health Law Article 27-F (sections 2780 through 2787) gives HIV-related information stricter confidentiality than ordinary medical records. A healthcare provider, laboratory, insurer, or government agency cannot disclose HIV testing information without specific written authorization from the tested person, except in narrow statutory exceptions. The Article 27-F consent form is separate from a general HIPAA release. Unlawful disclosure can trigger civil and criminal penalties. Anonymous testing is available at public health department clinics — no name is recorded. A positive result triggers optional partner notification assistance through NYS DOH without revealing the original patient's identity to partners."
